data.name: Thinkage.MainBoss.Database§UnitSummary_Comment
data.value: Permission to read a small subset of information from Unit records. For example, this allows you to see the Unit Category of units but not any work orders associated with the unit or any money information associated with the unit (e.g. replacement cost). The amount of information available is partly determined by what other security roles you have. Often, UnitSummary is useful for people whose primary interest is some other part of MainBoss (e.g. work orders or requests). (UnitSummary is not needed if a user already has the Unit or UnitView security role.)

data.name: Thinkage.MainBoss.Database§UnitView_Comment

data.name: Thinkage.MainBoss.Database§WorkOrder_Comment
data.value: Permission to create and modify work orders. This automatically gives you limited access to other information in MainBoss. For example, you can browse the Items table, but not view the contents of Items records (unless you have additional roles). Similarly, you can browse Inside and Outside Labor records, but cannot see the actual money amounts associated with them (unless you have additional security roles). To deal with item costs on work orders, a user needs the AccountingWorkOrder security role; to deal with labor costs, a user needs AccountingView.

data.name: Thinkage.MainBoss.Database§WorkOrderAssignSelf_Comment
data.value: Permission to assign work orders with "Self Assign". If you have no other permissions, WorkOrderAssignSelf only lets you deal with work orders which have been assigned to you and work orders that are not assigned to anyone.

data.name: Thinkage.MainBoss.Database§WorkOrderAssignSelf_Desc
data.value: Assign unassigned work orders to self

data.name: Thinkage.MainBoss.Database§WorkOrderClose_Comment
data.value: Permission to close work orders with "Close Work Order" and "Close Work Order (With Comment)"; also to add comments with "Add Work Order Comment". Also allows user to view much of the information on work orders. Viewing money amounts (e.g. labor costs) requires additional security roles (e.g. AccountingWorkOrder). WorkOrderClose only lets you deal with your assigned work orders. If WorkOrderClose is combined with WorkOrderView, the user can close any work order, not just assigned ones. (WorkOrderClose is not needed if a user already has the WorkOrder security role.)

data.name: Thinkage.MainBoss.Database§WorkOrderFulfillment_Comment
data.value: Permission to turn existing item demands into actuals, and to enter other information related to finishing a job (e.g. downtime and closing code). If you have no other permissions, WorkOrderFulfillment only lets you deal with your assigned work orders. You may want to combine WorkOrderFulfillment with AccountingWorkOrder to allow a user to specify and edit the cost of work order materials and outside labor. If WorkOrderFulfillment is combined with WorkOrderView, it allows the user to specify finishing information for any work order. (WorkOrderFulfillment is not needed if a user already has the WorkOrder security role.)

data.name: Thinkage.MainBoss.Database§WorkOrderFulfillment_Desc
data.value: Actualize information on an existing work order

data.name: Thinkage.MainBoss.Database§WorkOrderSummary_Comment
data.value: Permission to see a small subset of the information in a work order. This does not include information about labor or materials (unless you have additional security roles). Often, this security role is useful for people whose primary interest is tracking requests. (WorkOrderSummary is not needed if a user already has WorkOrderView or WorkOrder.)

data.name: Thinkage.MainBoss.Database§WorkOrderSummary_Desc
